In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki announced several upcoming events and initiatives. President Biden will be traveling to Boise, Idaho, Sacramento and Long Beach, California, and Denver, Colorado to highlight the impact of climate change on wildfires and the need for investments in climate change mitigation and infrastructure. Psaki also mentioned that Vice President Kamala Harris will be meeting with abortion and reproductive health providers and patients to discuss the impact of Texas Senate Bill 8. In addition, HHS Secretary Becerra released a plan to lower prescription drug prices, and the President will be delivering a speech later in the day to announce new measures to combat COVID-19, including a vaccine mandate for federal workers. Psaki also addressed questions about the recent evacuation efforts in Afghanistan, the nomination of David Chipman as ATF director, and other topics.